dataList.name: Jeff Bezos
dataList.description: Jeffrey Preston Bezos is an American entrepreneur, media proprietor, investor, computer engineer, and commercial astronaut. He is the founder and executive chairman of Amazon, where he previously served as the president and CEO.

dataList.name: Elon musk
dataList.description: Elon Reeve Musk FRS is an entrepreneur and business magnate. He is the founder, CEO, and Chief Engineer at SpaceX; early-stage investor, CEO, and Product Architect of Tesla, Inc.; founder of The Boring Company; and co-founder of Neuralink and OpenAI.

dataList.name: Steve Jobs
dataList.description: Steven Paul Jobs was an American business magnate, industrial designer, media proprietor, and investor.

dataList.name: Mark Zuckerbeg
dataList.description: Mark Elliot Zuckerberg is an American media magnate, internet entrepreneur, and philanthropist. He is known for co-founding the social media website Facebook and its parent company Meta Platforms, of which he is the chairman, chief executive officer, and controlling shareholder.

dataList.name: Bill Gates
dataList.description: William Henry Gates III is an American business magnate, software developer, investor, author, and philanthropist. He is a co-founder of Microsoft, along with his late childhood friend Paul Allen.

dataList.name: Johnny Depp
dataList.description: John Christopher Depp II is an American actor, producer, and musician. He is the recipient of various accolades, including a Golden Globe Award and a Screen Actors Guild Award, in addition to nominations for three Academy Awards and two British Academy Film Awards.

dataList.name: Emma Watson
dataList.description: Emma Charlotte Duerre Watson is an English actress and activist. She is known for her roles in both blockbusters and independent films, as well as for her women's rights work.

dataList.name: Brad Pitt
dataList.description: William Bradley Pitt is an American actor and film producer. He is the recipient of various accolades, including an Academy Award, a British Academy Film Award, and two Golden Globe Awards

dataList.name: Charles Chaplin
dataList.description: Sir Charles Spencer Chaplin Jr. KBE was an English comic actor, filmmaker, and composer who rose to fame in the era of silent film. He became a worldwide icon through his screen persona, the Tramp, and is considered one of the film industry's most important figures.

dataList.name: Morgan Freeman
dataList.description: Morgan Freeman is an American actor, director, and narrator. Noted for his distinctive deep voice, Freeman is known for his various roles in a wide variety of film genres.
